               <person xml:id="MA_Gaskell_Holland">
                  <persName ref="#MA_Gaskell_Holland">
                     <surname type="paternal">Gaskell</surname>
                     <surname type="married">Holland</surname>
                     <forename>Marianne</forename>
                     <addName>MA</addName>
                  </persName>
                  <birth>
                     <date when="1834-09-12">September 12 1834</date><placeName ref="#Manchester">Manchester, UK</placeName>/>
                  </birth>
                  <death>
                     <date when="1920"></date>
                     <placeName/>
                  </death>
                  <note type="bio" resp="#mjk">
                     <p>The Gaskells’ first surviving daughter, born <date when="1834-09-12">September 12, 1834</date>. Marianne is the subject of most of the diary, and is described as <q>gentle</q>. She was the only one of Gaskell’s daughters to become a mother herself, though she was still unmarried at the time of Gaskell’s death.</p>
                  </note>
               </person>
